  "issue_title": "M1 exit: system prompt SHA is identical across full-stack restart",
  "issue_body": "## Goal\n\nProve the assembled system prompt is **deterministic across restarts** \u2014\nsame config, same hydrated state \u2192 same SHA. Closes the \"no silent prompt\ndrift between runs\" requirement from M1.\n\n## What to build\n\n- Compute and log the SHA of the fully-assembled system prompt on every\n  boot (after all hydration: persona, memory recall, tool list, channel\n  context, voice mode, etc.)\n- Surface the SHA in `/api/health` and `genie-ctl status`\n- Add an integration test that boots the stack twice from the same config\n  and confirms identical SHAs\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] System-prompt SHA logged at boot\n- [ ] SHA visible via `/api/health` and `genie-ctl status`\n- [ ] Test boots stack 2\u00d7 from identical config \u2192 asserts identical SHA\n- [ ] Any change to prompt assembly logic is now observable by SHA delta\n\n## Context\n\nTracks one of the five M1 exit criteria from the README roadmap. See\n[`Roadmap` in README.md](../blob/main/README.md#roadmap).",
